        <p>&#160;</p>
        <h4>Auto Complete</h4>
        <p>Enable Auto Complete in the Text Editor's local toolbar. Then type in the Text Editor:</p>
        <p>
            <img src="../../Images/TestPlans/Flare/InternalTextEditor/InternalTextEditor--AutoComplete.png" />
        </p>
        <p>&#160;</p>
        <p>Test Cases:</p>
        <ul class="checkbox">
            <li>Entering &lt; invokes an auto complete box allowing you to select any tag</li>
            <li>Entering &lt; followed by text filters the items in the auto complete box to those that match the text you continue to type</li>
            <li>Using auto complete to enter the following tags will automatically add the corresponding closing tag and place the insertion point between them so you can continue typing within that tag: p, h1, h2, h3, h4, h5, h6, div, etc.</li>
            <li>Using auto complete to enter the following tags will create a self-closing tag and place the insertion point in an appropriate attribute upon auto completing:&#160;img (src), MadCap:concept (term), etc</li>
            <li>Using auto complete to create certain tag structures like a MadCap:dropDown text should only allow you to insert dropDown tags in the appropriate structure</li>
            <li>Similarly, using auto complete to create a table should only allow you to create tag structure to create a valid table</li>
            <li>Inserting a space in front of the &gt; of an opening tag will allow you to select various appropriate attributes (class, style, etc)</li>
            <li>
                <p>If at any point while typing directly in the Text Editor, you create invalid markup, a Warning will appear in the toolbar:</p>
                <p>
                    <img src="../../Images/TestPlans/Flare/InternalTextEditor/InternalTextEditor--Warning.png" />
                </p>
            </li>
            <li><span class="KeyboardShortcut">Up Arrow</span> and <span class="KeyboardShortcut">Down Arrow</span> keys can be used to navigate up and down through the auto compete list</li>
            <li><span class="KeyboardShortcut">Tab</span> or <span class="KeyboardShortcut">Enter</span> can be used to select item from the auto complete list</li>
        </ul>
        <p>&#160;</p>
    </body>
